About
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

This is command line program that reads all user files from provided folder.
It reports statistical results about airline purchaseList.
Files' names should be integer numbers that represent user id.
Desired results will be printed in command line interface.



Instructions on how to run this program
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Prerequisites:
- Windows 7 or later
- Java 8 or later
- A command line interface (like Windows CMD)

Steps to run the program:
1) Open command line interface.

2) Run airStat.jar file using cli command below:
   "{folder of Java installation}\jdk1.8.0\bin\java.exe" -Dfile.encoding=windows-1253 -jar "{absolute path of jar file}"

   Here lays an example of this command:
   "C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.8.0\bin\java.exe" -Dfile.encoding=windows-1253 -jar "C:\Users\user\Desktop\Aircloak test\implementation\airStatsCLI\dist\airStats.jar"

3) Provide folder's absolute path, as it will be asked.



Program results
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

| key              | value   | count |
--------------------------------------
| Airline purchase | 150.0   | 10    |
| Airline purchase | 10000.0 | 520   |

min: 150.0
max: 10000.0
average: 5075.0
median:10000.0



Explanation of taken approach
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Approach that used for this project most simple.
Just created command line program that prints the results in console, so to be simple to run.



